<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 3:55PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Fergus
County through 445 PM MDT...
At 354 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 25
miles northeast of Roy, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Very heavy rainfall is also likely with
this storm.
Locations impacted include...
Valentine and areas near James Kipp Campground
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
